{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2012}} {{Infobox person | name = Bonnie Hart | image = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Queensland]], [[Australia]] | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = Australian | residence = | education = | other_names = | occupation = | known_for = [[Intersex human rights]] activist and president of the [[Androgen Insensitivity Syndrome Support Group Australia]] | television = | website = {{URL|www.aissga.org.au}} }} '''Bonnie Hart''' is an artist, film maker, and [[intersex human rights]] activist, born with [[androgen insensitivity syndrome]] and president of the [[Androgen Insensitivity Syndrome Support Group Australia]]. Hart performs nationally and internationally, and speaks on intersex issues nationally and internationally. In 2016, Australia's ''[[SX News|Gay News Network]]'' included her in their "25 LGBTI people to watch in 2017".<ref name="watch-2017" /><ref>{{cite web | url = https://oii.org.au/24704/intersex-inclusion-2014-sydney-mardi-gras-parade/ | title = Intersex inclusion in the 2014 Sydney Mardi Gras Parade | work = [[Organisation Intersex International Australia]] | date = 3 March 2014}}</ref>
== Early life == Hart describes how she was told she experienced "heteronormative sexual training from a really early age", through multiple [[intersex medical interventions]]. Despite giving consent as a child, she felt unaware of the lifelong implications.<ref name="copland2016">{{Cite web| last = Copland| first = Simon| title = The medical community's approach to intersex people is still primarily focused on 'normalising' surgeries| work = SBS| date = 15 December 2016| accessdate = 2017-01-19| url = http://www.sbs.com.au/topics/sexuality/agenda/article/2016/12/15/medical-communitys-approach-intersex-people-still-primarily-focused-normalising}}</ref> Hart describes how stigma "sets the scene" for such interventions, "There’s a fear that people will be maladjusted because their bodies are different, and that fear teamed with the ignorance of the realities of what it’s like to live as an adult with those bodies without surgery, kind of perpetuates a surgical intervention process".<ref name = "watch-2017" /> Growing up, Hart did not know that her sister, [[Phoebe Hart]], also had androgen insensitivity syndrome.<ref name="phart2012">{{Cite news| last = Graham| first = Liz| title = I'm proud to be a hermaphrodite| work = body+soul| date = 2 February 2012| url = http://www.bodyandsoul.com.au/sex+relationships/wellbeing/im+proud+to+be+a+hermaphrodite,16555}}</ref>
== Career ==
Hart is a "high-energy avant-garde performer" and multidisciplinary artist, assembling digital and analog filmmaking, music, and visual art.<ref name="venting">{{cite web| url = http://www.ventinggallery.com/bonnie-hart-bio/ | title = Bonnie Hart Bio | work = Venting Gallery | accessdate = 2017-01-19}}</ref> She is a cofounder of Venting Gallery and the Foundation for Contemporary Music and Culture in Brisbane, Queensland, and performs with bands including X-wave and the Unaustralians.<ref name="venting" /><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.collapseboard.com/reviews/live-reviews/the-audio-pollen-social-club-199-boundary-street-west-end-brisbane-10-02-13/ | title = The Audio Pollen Social Club @ 199 Boundary Street, West End, Brisbane, 10.02.13 | work = Collapse Board | date = 26 February 2013}}</ref> In the autobiographical documentary ''[[Orchids, My Intersex Adventure]]'', Hart and her sister face the traumatic emotional scars from early operations and the secrecy associated with them.<ref name="autobio">{{cite web | work = ATOM Awards | url = http://www.firsthandfilms.com/index.php?film=1000334 | title = First Hand Films 'Interview with Phoebe Hart'' | location = Melbourne, Australia | accessdate = 26 October 2010}}</ref><ref name="synopsis">{{cite web | work = Orchids, My Intersex Adventure | url = http://www.orchids-themovie.com/synopsis.html | title = Film Synopsis | date = 3 October 2010 | accessdate = 26 October 2010}}</ref>
== Activism == Hart is president of the [[Androgen Insensitivity Syndrome Support Group Australia]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://aissga.org.au | title = What's new with the AISSG Australia? | work = [[Androgen Insensitivity Syndrome Support Group Australia]]}}</ref> She has appeared in numerous short videos, including for QLife and the [[National LGBTI Health Alliance]],<ref>{{cite web | url = https://oii.org.au/28856/bonnie-qlife/ | title = Bonnie Hart talks about intersex | work = [[Organisation Intersex International Australia]] | date = 27 May 2015}}</ref> and [[Special Broadcasting Service|SBS]].<ref name="chaleyer2015">{{Cite news| last = Chaleyer| first = Rani| title = Intersex: the I in LGBTI| work = [[Special Broadcasting Service|SBS The Feed]] | date = 10 March 2015| url = http://www.sbs.com.au/news/thefeed/story/intersex-i-lgbti}}</ref><ref name="carpenter2015">{{Cite news| last = Carpenter| first = Morgan| authorlink = Morgan Carpenter | title = Comment: 'Curing' intersex is damaging and common| work = [[Special Broadcasting Service|SBS The Feed]] | date = 16 March 2015 | url = http://www.sbs.com.au/news/article/2015/03/16/comment-curing-intersex-damaging-and-common}}</ref> and is widely interviewed,<ref name="copland2016" /><ref>{{Cite news| last = Busby| first = Cec| title = Intersex advocates address findings of Senate Committee into involuntary sterilisation| work = Gay News Network| date = 28 October 2013| url = http://gaynewsnetwork.com.au/news/intersex-advocates-address-findings-of-senate-committee-into-involuntary-sterilisation-12237.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.starobserver.com.au/news/national-news/new-south-wales-news/senate-committee-wants-end-to-intersex-sterilisation/111708 | title = Senate Committee wants end to intersex sterilisation | publisher = [[Star Observer]] | date = 29 October 2013 | access-date = 2016-05-16 }}</ref> including on national television.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.abc.net.au/rampup/articles/2